The paper deals with attacks against binary code authorship identification, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also uses supervised machine learning techniques, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with modifying input binaries while maintaining functionality, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper uses adversarial techniques, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
